This article is a statement from the White House Office of the Press Secretary, announcing an executive order regarding the order of succession within the Department of Commerce. The order designates certain officials to act as the Secretary of Commerce in the event that the Secretary is unable to perform their duties. The designated officials include the Deputy Secretary of Commerce, General Counsel of the Department of Commerce, Under Secretaries, Chief Financial Officer, and the Boulder Laboratories Site Manager, among others. The order also includes exceptions and revokes previous executive orders on the same subject. The statement concludes by stating that the order does not create any enforceable rights or benefits.